    "Its core goals are to promote the safe and responsible development and use of AI while regulating the creation and use of AI technologies that endanger national security, health, and safety.",
    "It aims to address issues like opacity, complexity, bias, unpredictability, and autonomy in AI systems to guarantee fundamental human rights and spur legislative initiatives.",
    "Now, the European Parliament must discuss details with the European Union Council and European Commission before enacting this regulatory proposal into law.",
    "The final legislation will likely be a compromise between the three institutions' differing original drafts, a process estimated to take around two years before the act comes into force.",
    "Federal agencies in the U.S. are enhancing oversight on various issues related to AI."
